Kate and Prince William's whirlwind tour of the Caribbean has been a success, with the royals being able to focus on key issues close to their heart, renew the Crown's ties with these Caribbean nations and meet hundreds of people. However, it was also marred by protests, criticism and a few PR misfires, as noted by royal expert Russell Myers. While the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge were welcomed by hundreds of cheering well-wishers in Belize, Jamaica and The Bahamas, some of their visits also featured "pitfalls" in which the pair fell at times, Mr Myers believes. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES ON THE ROYAL FAMILY...